Package it.polimi.ingsw.view.clientSide.viewCore.data.dataClasses

Class ViewBoard

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.view.clientSide.viewCore.data.ViewObject
it.polimi.ingsw.view.clientSide.viewCore.data.dataClasses.ViewBoard
All Implemented Interfaces:
ClientAddressable, Addressable
public class ViewBoard
extends ViewObject
Class to represent the board. There will be no more than one instance in each client. It extends ViewObject. This class contains the Board with all its ViewCell and gives also the possibility to mark a Cell as "selected". No more than one Cell should be selected at the same time.
Author:
giorgio
See Also:
ViewCell, ViewObject

    • find

      public static ViewObject find​(@NotNull @NotNull java.lang.String id) throws NotFoundException, WrongViewObjectException
      Method that will search the object with the passed id; if it doesn't exists then try to create it. If the searched id is referring to a ViewBoard then: if exists an instance of the Board, then it'll return it; else it'll instantiate a new ViewBoard and will return it.
      Parameters:
      id - (String, the toString result of the searched Object)
      Returns:
      (The searched Object)
      Throws:
      NotFoundException - (If it doesn't find the object and cannot build it)
      WrongViewObjectException - (If the object is not of this Class).

    • populate

      public static ViewObject populate​(@NotNull @NotNull ServerSendDataEvent data)
      Method called when arriving a ServerSendDataEvent containing the information to build a new ViewBoard. If there already is an instance of the ViewBoard, it'll do nothing but returning it, else it'll construct a new ViewBoard -with the given information- and returns it.
      Parameters:
      data - (the Event arrived)
      Returns:
      (the new object created)

    • populate

      public static ViewObject populate​(BoardState state)
      Method called when arriving a BoardState containing the information to build a new ViewBoard or containing a representation of the state of the Board. If doesn't already exist an instance of the ViewBoard, it'll construct it. It set the instance of the ViewBoard to represent the same state given by the state parameter.
      Parameters:
      state - (the BoardStatus to be represented)
      Returns:
      (the ViewBoard correctly updated)
